      "content": "Copy that. We've been reviewing the upcoming mission roadmap. It looks like there are two high-priority seismic sensor deployments and a high-resolution panoramic scan of the Jezero crater rim scheduled for next week. \n\nClosing down now means we'll miss those entirely, and the rover will basically be a brick sitting in the dust until a potential recovery mission in 2-3 years (which isn't guaranteed). Are you sure there's no way to reroute power to stay partially active for those tasks?",
